# Bootstrap Carousel Responsive Implementation

## Core Principles

When implementing responsive Bootstrap carousels that show different numbers of items based on screen size:

- **Use separate carousels** for desktop and mobile rather than hiding items
- **Leverage Bootstrap display utilities** (`d-none d-md-block`, `d-md-none`)
- **Maintain proper carousel functionality** with independent controls
- **Follow Bootstrap's responsive breakpoints** (≥768px for desktop)
- **Ensure clean separation** between mobile and desktop experiences

## Implementation Pattern

### HTML Structure: Two Separate Carousels

```html
<!-- Desktop Carousel (2 items per slide) - Hidden on mobile -->
<div id="main_slider_desktop" class="carousel slide d-none d-md-block" data-ride="carousel">
  <div class="carousel-inner">
    <div class="carousel-item active">
      <div class="row">
        <!-- Service 1 -->
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <div class="box_section active">
            <h3 class="tile_text">Service Title</h3>
            <p class="lorem_text">Service description</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- Service 2 -->
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <div class="box_section">
            <h3 class="tile_text">Another Service</h3>
            <p class="lorem_text">Another service description</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <a class="carousel-control-prev" href="#main_slider_desktop" role="button" data-slide="prev">
    <i class="fa fa-angle-left"></i>
  </a>
  <a class="carousel-control-next" href="#main_slider_desktop" role="button" data-slide="next">
    <i class="fa fa-angle-right"></i>
  </a>
</div>

<!-- Mobile Carousel (1 item per slide) - Hidden on desktop -->
<div id="main_slider_mobile" class="carousel slide d-md-none" data-ride="carousel">
  <div class="carousel-inner">
    <div class="carousel-item active">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
          <div class="box_section active">
            <h3 class="tile_text">Service Title</h3>
            <p class="lorem_text">Service description</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <a class="carousel-control-prev" href="#main_slider_mobile" role="button" data-slide="prev">
    <i class="fa fa-angle-left"></i>
  </a>
  <a class="carousel-control-next" href="#main_slider_mobile" role="button" data-slide="next">
    <i class="fa fa-angle-right"></i>
  </a>
</div>
```

## Key Bootstrap Classes

### Display Utilities:
- **`d-none d-md-block`**: Hidden on mobile, visible on desktop (≥768px)
- **`d-md-none`**: Hidden on desktop, visible on mobile (<768px)

### Grid Classes:
- **`col-md-6`**: 50% width on desktop (≥768px)
- **`col-12`**: 100% width on all screen sizes

## CSS Requirements

### Desktop and Mobile Carousel Styles:
```css
/* Apply styles to both carousels */
#main_slider_desktop .carousel-control-prev,
#main_slider_desktop .carousel-control-next,
#main_slider_mobile .carousel-control-prev,
#main_slider_mobile .carousel-control-next {
    width: 65px;
    height: 65px;
    background: #404040;
    opacity: 1;
    font-size: 30px;
    color: #ffffff;
    border-radius: 100%;
}

#main_slider_desktop a.carousel-control-prev,
#main_slider_mobile a.carousel-control-prev {
    position: absolute;
    left: -30px;
    top: 65%;
    background: #367d99;
}

#main_slider_desktop a.carousel-control-next,
#main_slider_mobile a.carousel-control-next {
    position: absolute;
    right: -30px;
    top: 65%;
}
```

### Mobile-Specific Responsive Styles:
```css
@media (max-width: 575px) {
    #main_slider_desktop a.carousel-control-prev,
    #main_slider_mobile a.carousel-control-prev,
    #main_slider_desktop a.carousel-control-next,
    #main_slider_mobile a.carousel-control-next {
        width: 40px;
        height: 40px;
        font-size: 14px;
    }
    
    #main_slider_desktop a.carousel-control-prev,
    #main_slider_mobile a.carousel-control-prev {
        left: -17px;
    }
    
    #main_slider_desktop a.carousel-control-next,
    #main_slider_mobile a.carousel-control-next {
        right: -17px;
    }
}
```

